review: This place is the PITS! My wife and I used to go here all the time when she was pregnant with our 2 1/2 year old, and it was fine. We recently went there to grab a bite to eat now that the baby is getting a bit easier to manage, but OMG this place has gone down hill for sure! We ordered the Jack Daniels glazed ribs which came out over nuked and under glazed . . . The margarita's that we ordered were indescribably bad, so we decided to replace the, with beer . . . Strike #3 came in the form of a soapy taste in my beer followed by stomach cramps that persisted through the night. Do not waste your hard earned money here . . .  I would drive a little bit to the west and go to Moore's Tavern . . . Or to the east and go to the Fireside Grill . . . Despite the fact that this place is but a mile from our house, making it extremely convenient . . . WE WILL NOT BE GOING BACK TO THIS PLACE EVER!

I came here after my flight from LA to visit family.  I felt like having a pasta so I ordered their Chicken Picatta Pasta. They had a picture on the menu and it looked a lot. But when the waiter gave me the dish, it was soooo little. On the picture, there was a lot of pieces of chicken, red peppers and artichokes like there was an even amount of chicken, etc. and pasta. But the one I had was really little. It was more pasta than anything else. I don't care for capers that much but if it was a light flavor, I would eat it. They seemed to get that right out of everything. TGI Fridays should either change their pictures on the menu or have the chefs make it the way it supposed to look. The waiter was ok. He did come by to check on us once and the food came out slow (and there was no one around).  I'd only come here if there's nothing else open.

I don't care what anyone says about Fridays, this place has stepped its game up since the old days of suspenders, wacky pins, and over decorated interiors.  Yes there is still weird crap on the wall, but it's toned down about 9 notches.  Yes they're a chain, but they're on the level of the Olive Gardens, Outbacks, and Red Lobsters, not the Applebees and Chilis.  The food is good.  They have a wide variety.  The Jack Daniels menu is pretty solid.  Everything else is pretty creative and definitely not bland.  Loved the homemade loaded chips and the firecracker shrimp with asian slaw.  Awesome deals too.  Friendly staff and quick service.  I'm on on the Fridays bandwagon, yes.  Would typically give a 3 star for a chain, but this place has some poor reviews so far and Fridays has a bad rep that I don't agree with.

Ok I know its a chain and all but if you know what to order, you can have yourself a decent meal here. My failsafe recommendation: baby back ribs (and whatever 2 sides you want - substitutions allowed!). If you're lucky enough to get one of the seasoned waitresses here, you should have a relatively pain-free dining experience. I've seen people request to be seated in a certain waitstaff's area so keep an ear out to try to figure out which ones are good. I will update once I find out thwir names! Also, if you live in the area, there's always those buy 1 get 1 free entree coupons getting mailed to you.

Why is there always a problem getting seated here?? Any time we go this TGI, we stand at the front desk for a while before anyone even shows up to seat us!!  Tonight was no different. We got out for an early dinner so the place was not busy. All the staff seemed to be having a nice converstion while we were satanding in the front for 10 minutes!! Finally, one of the waiters spotted us and went and get the girl to seat us. No apology or any acknowledgement of the fact that we were standing there!!  As for the food, my wife and my son are enamored with JAck Danilels chicken and shrimp. Me, I could live without it so I tried one of the newer items on the menu, Salmon with Langostinos. The taste was ok. Nothing to rite home about and the portion was tiny. Something annoys me about paying 19.99 for anything in TGI's but I just did so shame on me!!
Typical chain spot.  We like to go during Happy Hour when the prices are just right for appetizers.

THIS PLACE SUCKS! The bar smells like vomit and the bartender seemed like he hated his job. I ordered the korean steak tacos and it was basically salad stuffed into a stale taco shell with barely any steak, WORST FOOD EVER! I wouldve rather went to applebees :-/
This place is terrible! It smells bad, the service is terrible and food isn't cooked through never coming back here again. Picking Applebee's any day over this dumpster.
Tried giving this place a second chance What a big fukn mistake Stay clear of this place Off to Applebee's

Bar service weak-- runs out of items to complete an order, manager does not address this issue, if you see a manager. Brings salsa but not the chips, no avocado to complete a sandwich, can they not take money from petty cash send someone to the store? customer should not have to change their order to accommodate a restaurant.

Worst experience every!!! place was empty but some how took 20min to get a seat and another 30 before we seen a waitress. Didn't have a wedge for the wedge salad.  Korean tacos had wilted lettuce on it, which wasn't even supposed to be on it.  Still waiting on my water and my change from the bill I handed the waitress 20minutes ago

This place is a disaster! Went there on a sunday for a school fundraiser. The host was rude and had no idea about the fundraiser. Crowd of people waiting to be seated... with a restaurant that was, at best, 40% full. Empty tables everywhere. We waited 10 minutes and left when an angry customer demanded to see the manager. Not worth the effort.  As a side observation, it smelled dirty too. The wait staff does not look professional. Won't be back.
this location was part of operation swill...whats wrong with people, they are always crowded. do your research they weren't serving what you thought!!!

Went there after a writing/recording session with my fellow musician pals during happy hour on the weekend. Usually our normal pattern. Not anymore though. Not after the great burger escape. Flashback: Three pals go into Fridays. Order two burgers and chicken fingers. Nothing really difficult. Not that hard to make. Instructions on the box type of deal. One burger comes out. Black. Asked for it medium. All good. Will endure. Tastes like charcoal crapped out charcoal in meat form. Fries taste like salt sticks. Heart attack by age 31. Second burger comes out. Cue 'great burger escape' theme. Two patties on this bertha of burgers. One of which hasn't reached full size yet. It's on the bottom. Add water to expand. Never added water. Reminds me of those sponges in the bath tub. Those were great. First patty is hanging on a 80 degree angle onto the plate. They missed. They missed the burger. Then they all decided to "do it live" and not fix it. It would've took 3 seconds.  Those 3 seconds were too valuable to TGI Fridays.  The burger patty stared at us. You know why they put it under a bun? So you don't have to see what you're eating. You don't want to see that. Well, we did. We stared at it for awhile. Waiting for it to move. It did a little bit. Cheese bubble. Popped. Looks delicious? No. Looks like dog toy.  Sorry Fridays. Uploading a picture for all the world to see the great burger escape. Because $60 for three people is pretty lame. But at least we can never come back and get a joke out of it.

Took my diabetic child here one day as a treat after soccer. We were seated and after 25 minutes nor a single waiter or waitress attended to us. I left and took her to Perkins across the seat to avoid her suffering from lack of eating. Pathetic this place is ....

I think we all know what type of food we are going to be getting when we go to a place like TGI Fridays.  Depending on how much of a foodie you are will be how you rate a chain family restaurant.  With that in mind the things that I like to differentiate places that are chains is usually the service.  The service that I have always had at this Fridays is polite professional and helpful.  I was here on a weekday and sat down at the bar and was again met with friendly staff.  I'm sure everyone has their days but my experience has always been positive.   Another thing that I have noticed with TGI Fridays is depending on the time and day you go you can get whatever you want for a fairly low price per todays standards.  I ordered a Miller Lite 16oz and the Nachos Grande and my bill without tip was $7.00.  Everything was half price off at the time I was there.  I didn't believe my eyes.  TGI Fridays at certain times can be cheaper than fast food and barely more when including the tip.  Assuming you have good tipping practices!  Stop in if you want friendly service and you won't overpay for it.

The good: it was Sunday at 1 and we got a seat immediately. The server was attentive. The Mac and cheese bites were very good.  The soso: the Thai pork tacos were more Korean than Thai. The fries were OK but the oil in which they were fried was odd. Not stale or rancid. But odd.  The bad:  the chicken Cesar salad dressing is a vinaigrette. Cheap wooden plates to serve sloppy burger so the grease is every where. The aioli was spread on the bun so that got soggy really quickly.  Won't return here.

Very disappointing from the start.  First when we arrived there were a lot of employees hanging around at the host desk ... Shouldn't they be working.  We ordered jack Daniels app which is a chicken dish. My husband bit into one and it was a shrimp. good thing I did not get that one or I would have went into shock since I am allergic. Really shrimp in a chicken dish... They seriously (I am not kidding ) could have killed me. To be on the safe side I ran to the car and took a benedryl.  We spoke to the manager who replied "that's odd". Ok how about a little caring reply, again since I could have went into shock. He was all laid back about it.... What a jerk especially caused my throat still feels like it is closing up a little.  When the two app's arrived to begin with we asked the food runner for side plates and napkins...... Never got them. We had to track down another server for them. By this time our buffalo wings were cold.  We had the jack Daniels chicken sandwich which was yummy. I would definitely have that again  Our server was nice but he left all our Dirty plates on the table and never cleaned them. When we left they were, again, a ton of employees at the host desk chatting away. At other restaurants , including other Friday's , they open the doors for you. But not here. Seems like they can not be bothered.... To busy talking I guess  My husband knows the general manager from when they worked together a long time ago. I wonder what he would think of this.

Good afternoon, The reason I'm giving TGI Fridays 5 stars is for the following, I had an issue with my last visit , they showed that they really do care about their customers , will go the extra mile too keep their customers happy. Also the food is good, we all know what kind of food we are going too get before we go inside. The servers are very pleasant,helpful and polite .

Terrible, Terrible, and more terrible !! Service is poor. Right off the bat, ordered a beer and my wife had water. Came to the table and spilt some of the beer on the table top and just left. Had to flag another server to give us some napkins. The food was horrible. Rack of baby back ribs, all bone and some cold French fries. My wife had chicken fajitas, barely eatable. Stay away ! They should close and have Applebee's  or another chain take over. Yuck

I've come here a few times with my boyfriend and we never really had any complaints. Foods good, service is always friendly. But my last visit totally blew my mind. We went a little late. Around 11:30. We sat in a booth by the bar area. We were the only people sat at the tables in the bar room but there were 4 people at the bar. 2 guys and another couple. Right as soon as we entered the room the 2 guys started yelling. Like literally screaming. The bartender was laughing with them. My server told me they're regulars and do this every weekend but nothing more. As the meal went on their conversations got louder and more graphic. Talking about sex and showing each other nude pictures of their girlfriends, yelling about each other's moms. All about 10 feet from my table with my boyfriend. The bartender kept telling them to stop but in that "ha ha you guys are crazy" kind of way. They started to threaten to whip out their penises and the bartender kept laughing and telling them to stop. Then They did! These two guys took out their penises at the tgi Friday's bar and asked the bartender if she wanted to see them hard. She laughed and told them if they don't stop she really will kick them out. Idk how things work over there but I work at another restaurant in the area and if someone even got 1/10th as drunk as those guys, theyd be out. She never kicked them out after they whipped their privates out. They stayed and continued their disgusting and loud conversation. Later on the host came over and gave us 2 free appetizer cards just in case we were offended by anything we heard/saw. Which was nice, he was a very very nice guy. I just cannot believe I saw 2 dicks while eating at a restaurant and they were allowed to stay.

Always come here. A few sentences are said to explain it. Usually ok you might get a server that is young but you feel bad because their young. Last time ( a week ago) I ordered the Jack Daniels Burger . There was no Jack Daniels Sauce. Sad. Really?
It was too cold.   When we asked to turn up the heat, they must have done it in another part of the restaurant.  C'mon it's winter, let's use the heat!

People should know that the kitchen staff does not wear gloves while preparing food, even those who mix your salads. They get most of their food frozen and is simply reheated, and their soup comes in a plastic bag. They don't stop serving alcohol to people who become belligerent, and have the most vile people at their bar all day, making for an uncomfortable dining experience. I can't even explain how disgusting it is, but people should really eat there at their own risk. Honestly, any other place you could find to eat would be better. In order to pass health regulations, they get advance notice and put on an act. They would be shut down immediately if people knew the truth. I'm hopeful that people will catch on one day and maybe we can have a decent restaurant open up.
I refuse to spend time writing a long review of what's wrong with this place...This place sucks!

Got take out from this location just now, and although the service was friendly, the one hostess had no idea about the "industry" night they were clearly advertising on a chalkboard in neon colors as soon as you walk in the restaurant. And the chicken in my pecan crusted chicken salad is clearly old and stale. My buffalo chicken tenders are delicious, though! I hope for better my next visit!

What can I say, we have been coming here for years.  While some "staple" menu items such as the oreo madness remain, they do regularly rotate some items. Stick to what they are good at like the JD items and you can't really go wrong, assuming they don't mess up your order. The good:  Craft beer cheese pretzels, black bean Burger and on a good day, grilled chicken fajitas, drinks, anything JD. The bad: This place regularly screws up things.  This time, they did not have guacamole so I asked for some avacado.  The picture I posted showed the avacado slices they provided.  These were improperly stored and were starting to spoil.   Service was slow.  No one here and over 20 minutes to get our food which is way past industry average ticket time. Also no greeter when we came in, and we had to play "let's find a waitress" to be seated"

You could just repeat the same review for Applebee's, Chili's, Ruby's, etc. It's a chain. Mediocre food, mediocre service, mediocre décor. As long as you don't order something that may take more knowledge to cook such as a steak, then the food is ok. It's not great, just ok. Deep fried this, deep fried that. Delve into the more complicated items like a steak and you will just be disappointed. You'll be lucky if your steak is cooked the way you asked for it. I've been down that road before. For me if I find that I have to go to a Fridays it's generally the Jack Daniels chicken I'll order. Chicken overcooked and dry of course, no surprise there. But at least I can get some moisture from the JD sauce.

Stopped here for a quick lunch. Bar was sticky and dirty. Lettuce in salad was rusty and old. Ordered a cheeseburger, was never asked what kind of cheese and the lettuce and tomato was mush! Had to ask twice for salt. No wonder there are only a handful of customers in here on a Friday afternoon. Never again!

If I can give this a zero star I would. This is the second time they messed up a takeout order. How hard is it to get it right. Always missing something. First time I realized it when I got home. Second time waiting here for one hour and missing 2 buffalo wings   If I could fax the order they would get it wrong. So frustrated. Incompetence is the exact wording. When you hire all high school kids with no experience and pay minimum wage, RESULTS= minimum service. Never again.
It is really bad service and will never eat her again waitresses were childish and some were even fighting in front of customers over a tip.

Food is fine.  Exactly what I expected from Fridays.  Service is horrific.  We used to come in on Sundays to watch football and couldn't find a seat. We hadn't been there in a while so decided to go in.  We sat at the bar and there were only a few people there.  After waiting 5 minutes the bartender  Markisha finally acknowledged us and took our drink order.  A couple minutes later another bartender Jennette came over and asked again.  Finally we got drinks. We then listened to Jeanette talk about how hung over she is and can't wait to get out of there.  There were a couple  of other inappropriate conversations we overheard as well.  Then we waited 10 minutes to order food. Not because they weren't paying attention but because they weren't there Customers walked in, sat down, and walked out because there was no bartender. One would return for a few minutes and then they would disappear again.
Like coming here for the appetizers!! They are just sooo good oh the drinks too!!! But over all good place to go

I didn't have any problems with he service, service was good, just as you expect it to be, I ordered the grill chicken with mash potatoes and tomatoes, I forgot the name of the fish but it was a flavorful dish, I wish it were a little more filling though because I was still craving for something, but all and all, everything was very good and I would return.

These four stars only because I know the person i'm going to. In last 2 months I used to go to Friday's couple times a week for lunch or early dinner, so would be honest if Kate/Katja the bartender, who us serving time to time tables, is in I would be the happiest person, would get exactly what I wanted pretty fast, but if it would be someone else, sorry, but I'll go to another place. The food is always great, as i would expect in Friday's, so for now I'm checking first is my favorite bartender at work or not, and only than I'll enjoy the visit.)

Ignorance Poor Management/Service walked out. It had been a long time since coming back to this place (a result of poor service / so so food). So last night at 930 after a long day at work exercise while bringing my son home from soccer practice we decided to give them another try.  Place was empty and the Yankees were on so I asked hostess if we could sit in the bar area. He Happily sat us in a booth within the bar area.  Waited 10 minutes and waitress told me that they can't have children at bar after 9 and offered to sit us outside of this area. Really. Wanted a nice meal glass of wine and to watch ball game with my son and was in a booth not at the bar which I would clearly understand. Imagine if they said that atMoore, Chapter House, Cabin....... No wonder the place was empty. Very poor business sense and I didn't want to sit in an empty restaurant area left with out ordering pissed again at this place.  This is my first negative comment on Yelp but it still pisses me off.  Now I won't go back as there are so many better more accommodating places in the area and will make same recommendation to friend. Dumb

We've been to this Friday's before and weren't very impressed with the food. We tried again due to the $10 all you can eat apps. The apps we chose were hit and miss. Boneless chicken wings were OK, the mozerella (sp?) were very good. The other three apps were bland. On this visit, we had the worst waiter we'ver EVER had at any restaraunt. This guy (Eric) should seriously consider a career path that doesn't require interacting with, you know, people. Slow service, no personallity, and it seemed he really didn't want to be there.  Based on our experience, and the majority of other one star reviews, this'll be the last trip to this particular Friday's.  We left the place at about 4:45 PM, and the parking lot was pretty much deserted...now I know why.

My wife and I have been coming to the Freehold TGIF for years usually just having a dinner and we've for the most part had a pleasant experience. Tonight on a Wednesday evening we decided on burgers which were so good that my wife ate the entire burger and fries, and used 2 napkins! And she wasn't hungry! She had the Jack Daniel's burger and I had the All American. I would definitely recommend their burgers!

Friday's. It's Friday. I wanted a burger so why not? I'm not big fan of Fridays, but I went so.... Party of two. Greeted by several hosts? I was asked three times by three different people if we were a party of two. Sat us at a two top - saw available booths, but I let it go. Was pretty cold in there too which made me extra anxious to wrap this meal up and go as quickly as possible. Burger was kinda pink- requested medium well.... Onion bacon jam is just some sautéed onions and old bacon. I left it untouched on my plate. Fries were salty. Like really salty.  The sirloin was decent.  Whiskey cake seemed dry. Kinda reminded me of a spice cake covered in a sauce. Unimpressive. All in all a disappointing meal. My waitress, was attentive and accommodating, as were all the members of the staff I encountered. I came home and polished my meal off with some Galeffi (Italian antacid)

This restaurant has been going downhill for a long time and has finally fallen altogether off my list. Ordered fajitas - took almost half an hour to come out, the tortillas were so stale they were flaking away and the dish was 90% rice with a couple of bits of meat thrown in. Everyone else was done eating by the time fresh tortillas came out and we were so hungry we just at the rice and meat without them. One star for poor service and food quality.

This place has gone downhill! Dirty, bathroom smelled like raw sewerage. Food Kids chicken fingers just ok Cobb salad ok Caesar salad with steak - awful! Steak was very very small Croutons were pepperidge farm quality Very disappointed  We will not be returning!

horrible service the general manager is the worst ever . been there a few times and seems like every time i go i get told kitchen crashes and i have to wait 45 minutes for boneless wings kinda sad restaurant but the general manager and her attitude is the worst im done with this restaurant for a very long time .

Came here today for a late lunch early dinner after a long day at a car dealership, O we were hungry and thought hey $10.00 endless apps why not... so we schlepped our tired butts over in the rain to T.G.I.F. Surprise!! endless apps are not just $10.00 pp- yep there is an up- charge of $1. and odd change when you ask for a refill of said appetizers. I couldn't find this in the small print or online but per our server this was the case, so YES it's 10.00 per person, but with an up-charge-- we passed. I can say, our server was really nice and attentive, but it was downhill from there and I blame the kitchen, because the restaurant and bar was not packed- at all. What we did order:  Green Bean Fries with Cucumber-Wasabi Dipping Sauce- Large enough to share and a real sleeper and by that I mean-they didn't sound appealing at all, but Mini-Me wanted them AND they were good!! the dipping sauce- YUM!! we asked for extra. Spinach & Queso Dip- Gross. Glob of what??  Came out lukewarm at best. The best that we three could tell, is it looked like the kitchen just plopped a cold spinach ball in the center of the little serving dish, kind of mashed it down and poured the "warm queso"  mixture on top w/ breadcrumbs, it wasn't even toasted. It was sooo lukewarm that I was able to hold the bowl in my hand- while I stirred the cheese and spinach to blend, and even then, as you can see from the pics-- that spinach is mighty green and spinachy. We ate some of the cheesy mix around the spinach because we were hungry, but it was already cold because the spinach was cold.  Dinner Side Salad- Came with my entree- it's salad. Entree- Hubby had the bacon cheeseburger- according to him it was -"just okay"-it was really pink in the middle more on the rare side and limp old bacon-eww. Mini-Me had the 1/2 rack of Jack Daniels ribs- they were dry and fries were super salty so- for a kid that loves her fries- she couldn't eat them. I ordered the French Dip which came with fries. The meat was really dry and jerky-ish, the bread was hard, even the onion dipping Au Jus couldn't save it because it was totally flavorless. There was very little meat, the cheese was dry and in the photo I attached I just opened up the sandwich and snapped the photo. Yes I ate the first 1/2 because I was hungry but left the second portion, I simply couldn't stomach it. 1 strawberry lemonade, 1 peach ice tea and 1 reg ice tea--  total for lunch $80.00+ change. We paid our bill and when we got into the car, my hubby and Mini-Me said - well, that was terrible. Now what I can say is our server was super nice but that really can't make up for the lousy food.

I used to love going to friday's... now, i'd rather go anywhere else. The energy of the place is about as exciting as eating food in a morgue. We ordered a steak which was so small, you could have ordered a burger that was bigger. To compliment that, it was charred on the edges so the only edible part was the middle, thus making the portion size that much smaller. My friend ordered sliders, that looked like one burger cut in 3 to make white castle burgers ( also burnt ) Then there comes my veggie avocado burger . The last words I remember hearing were... " you still want the avocado right?" which you'd think when saying yes, was definitive in it's being. Nope. No avocado on it even though I said yes. To make it even better, the fork which was taken from my plate after i finished my salad, was never replaced, so i ate my veggie burger and mashed potatoes with my steak knife. One would normally say, John, why didn't you just ask her for another? To which I would answer " why, yes, I would " but alas, she was nowhere to be found and didn't check up on us til we were practically finished. This is another restaurant that raises the cost of food, while making the mediocre food at best, while simultaneously making their portions so small you wonder what the hell you're paying for. Won't be back is an understatement

We came here for quick apps and a few beers and I'm very disappointed at how unclean it was. There were knats all over the menus and flies on the bar. My seat and surface in front of me was disgustingly sticky. I could maybe understand the lack of cleanliness on a busy Saturday night, but there's no excuse on a slow Wednesday evening. If you can't keep your bar even moderately clean, I wonder what your kitchen looks like...
Not very good service late on sundays!  Just bad management!  Food was terrible and took all day to get it!!  Waiter was very nice.
Food is okay and servers are usually helpful. I love the dirt cup from the kids menu. Pudding, crushed Oreos and gummy worms. Also it's a good place to go when you want to get a quick app.

I have to update my review ( removing one star) based off my visit today. My husband and I came in for a quick lunch. The server was really great about making sure we received our food quickly (she was awesome!) I ordered a simple turkey burger and sweet potato fries. Omg! That burger was dry and tasteless! The fried were a tad undercooked. I could've got a better burger at Wendy's and paid less money! When a restaurant can mess up something as simple as a burger and fries you have to reconsider your patronage to the establishment! Ugh!
Just had the best Black bean /avocado burger!Also we had a pretty nice ultimate margarita. Dazhon the bartender ,he was attentive and made a decent cocktail.

Today I was at TGI Fridays. It was a really bad experience with the service. There were so many tables empty and I had requested a table for 2 but was told that there was a 30 minute wait.  Therefore, I sat at the bar. Furthermore, the service time took so long. I ordered sizzling chicken and shrimp and they forgot the shrimp. All that was ordered was two cokes, nachos and the sizzling chicken and shrimp and it took over one hour for service. The person who was working at the bar had too much on his plate and it took a long time for everything. It was incredibly underwhelming and frustrating to have such bad service. Furthermore, it was a Saturday night but the place was empty. The food was not great tasting either. I would never go back there again. It was pathetic service and I was incredibly annoyed by it. TGIF is supposed to a be a sports bar but it did not even have the proper sports TV channels. It was a horrible experience and it completely ruined my evening.
Service was terrible!!!! Food was nasty!!! Daughter had a orange juice and it was sour. Place very dirty, and unorganized... Never again will I take my family here.
